==Reactions==
[[File:2016 Berlin Christmas market truck attack - after attack the 20-12-2016 02.jpg|thumb|Aftermath of the 2016 Berlin Christmas market truck attack, 20 December]]
Many world leaders offered condolences to Germany and the victims of the attack.<ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=http://europe.newsweek.com/berlin-attack-germany-angela-merkel-vladimir-putin-world-leader-reactions-afd-534118?rm=eu|title=How World Leaders Reacted to the Berlin Attack|last=Gidda|first=Mirren|date=20 December 2016|work=[[Newsweek]]|access-date=21 December 2016}}</ref>

National and international [[Right-wing politics|right-wing]] politicians laid blame for the attack on [[Chancellor of Germany|Federal Chancellor]] Angela Merkel and [[European migrant crisis|her refugee policies]] and "open door to migrants".<ref>"[http://www.reuters.com/article/us-germany-truck-czech-babis-idUSKBN149226 Czech finance minister says 'no place' for migrants in Europe]". Reuters. 20 December 2016.</ref><ref name="Joffe 2016 / Merkel refugee">{{cite web | last=Joffe | first=Josef | title=After Berlin, Angela Merkel's open door to migrants might slam shut | website=the Guardian | date=20 December 2016| url=http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/dec/20/angela-merkel-open-door-migrants-berlin-christmas-market-attack-refugee | accessdate=21 December 2016}}</ref><ref name="The Independent 2016 / MEP">{{cite news | title=German MP blames Angela Merkel for suspected terror attack in Berlin | website=[[The Independent]] | date=19 December 2016| url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/berlin-attack-angela-merkel-german-mp-blames-chancellor-for-lorry-deaths-latest-a7485486.html | accessdate=21 December 2016}}</ref><ref name="Hjelmgaard 2016 / Angelina">{{cite web | last=Hjelmgaard | first=Kim | title=Berlin attack puts pressure on Angela Merkel's political survival | website=USA Today | date=20 December 2016| url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2016/12/20/berlin-attack-piles-pressure-germanys-merkel-over-her-refugee-stance/95644704/ | accessdate=21 December 2016}}</ref><ref name="Oltermann 2016 / Merkel">{{cite web | last=Oltermann | first=Philip | title=Deadly attack on German soil is worst fear for Angela Merkel | website=[[The Guardian]] | date=20 December 2016| url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/dec/20/angela-merkel-supporters-fears-berlin-attack | accessdate=21 December 2016}}</ref><ref name="Reilly 2016 / populist">{{cite news | last=Reilly | first=Katie | title=How Europe's Rightwing Populists Reacted to Berlin Christmas Market Attack | website=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] | date=20 December 2016| url=http://time.com/4607711/europe-rightwing-populist-berlin-attack/ | accessdate=21 December 2016}}</ref> By contrast, several other national and international political commentators praised what they described as the cool-headed reaction of the Merkel administration, and condemned the right-wing reaction as dangerous.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zeit.de/politik/ausland/2016-12/internationale-medien-berlin-anschlag-weihnachtsmarkt|title=Internationale Medien zu Berlin: 'Merkel sollte standhaft bleiben – was immer der Preis ist'|date=21 December 2016|publisher=|via=[[Die Zeit]]|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.merkur.de/politik/anschlag-in-berlin-csu-scheuer-verteidigt-horst-seehofers-forderung-zr-7154744.html|title=„Nicht pietätlos“: Scheuer verteidigt Seehofers Flüchtlingsaussage|date=21 December 2016|publisher=|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/editorial-on-the-suspected-berlin-terror-attack-a-1126762.html|title=Commentary on the Berlin Attack: Our Strength|first=Spiegel Online, Hamburg|last=Germany|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/20/opinion/a-cruel-test-for-germany-and-for-europe.html|title=A Cruel Test for Germany, and Europe|date=21 December 2016|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/346c7412-c6ca-11e6-9043-7e34c07b46ef|title= The Berlin attack calls for strength and calm. German lives and values are under attack. Protect them both|publisher=FT.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/trump-criticised-response-berlin-attack-compared-unfavourably-obama-1597480|title=Trump criticised for response to Berlin attack and compared unfavourably with Obama|first=Harriet|last=Sinclair|date=20 December 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/voices/editorials/angela-merkel-berlin-christmas-market-afd-far-right-populism-refugees-a7486426.html|title=Angela Merkel should not be blamed for the massacre at the Berlin Christmas market|date=20 December 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/dec/21/berlin-christmas-market-terror-angela-merkel|title=Amid the bloody carnage left by hate, Angela Merkel is a beacon of sanity|date=21 December 2016|publisher=|via=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref>

A petition to award Urban the [[Order of Merit of the Federal Republic of Germany|Bundesverdienstkreuz]] had gathered over 2,500 signatures by the afternoon of 22 December.<ref>"[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/dec/22/berlin-christmas-market-attack-polish-truck-driver-lukasz-urban-germany-order-merit Calls for Polish truck driver killed in Berlin to receive order of merit]". ''The Guardian''. 22 December 2016.</ref>

[[Muslims]] and [[Christianity|Christians]] in Berlin held a [[vigil]] in solidarity with the victims of the attack.<ref>"[http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/12/20/live-coverage-scene-berlin-christmas-market-attack/ Live: vigil held for victims of Berlin Christmas market attack]". ''The Daily Telegraph''. 20 December 2016.</ref><ref>{{cite news | title=Muslime zeigen Solidarität mit Opfern von Berlin | url=https://www.welt.de/vermischtes/article160483287/Muslime-zeigen-Solidaritaet-mit-Opfern-von-Berlin.html | via=[[Die Welt]] | date=December 21, 2016 | accessdate=December 22, 2016|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title=Berlin lorry attack: Muslim community holds vigil for victims | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-38389333 | via=[[BBC News]] | date=December 21, 2016 | accessdate=December 22, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title=Berlin's Muslim community sends message of peace and solidarity after Christmas market attack | url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/berlin-attack-muslim-community-germany-message-peace-solidarity-christmas-market-a7488571.html | via=[[The Independent]] | date=December 21, 2016 | accessdate=December 22, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title='We love Germany' Berlin's Muslims hold peace vigil for Christmas market attack victims | url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/world/746214/Muslims-hold-vigil-berlin-terror-attack-christmas-market | via=[[Daily Express]] | date=December 21, 2016 | accessdate=December 22, 2016}}</ref>

